pullRequest.body:
Unify Scott Topologies, following on from #13201 and #16826.

Originally Mathlib had a notion of Ï‰-Scott Continuity and Ï‰-Scott Topology based on Chains for Ï‰-complete partial orders. Previously we introduced a notion of Scott Continuity and Scott Topology based on directed sets for arbitrary pre-orders (#2508). In #13201, we generalised our definition of Scott Continuity to include Ï‰-Scott Continuity as a special case. This PR continues that work by generalising our notion of Scott Topology to include Ï‰-Scott Topology as a special case.

`Topology.IsScott.scottContinuous_iff_continuous` and `Topology.IsScott.Ï‰scottContinuous_iff_continuous` have almost identical proofs and are presumably special cases of a more general result that I have not yet formulated. However I think this PR covers enough ground to be worth considering at this stage.

---
